<TITLE> Govt to train imams against terrorism </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 17 (bdnews24.com)  The government will start training Imams of mosques on the evils of religious militancy from this year, religious affairs minister told the parliament Sunday. Replying to a written question from Awami League MP Anu Ukil, Md Shahjahan Mia told the house that the government generally trained imams for 45 days at a training academy specialised for them. "One of the components of the training is to orient the imams to deliver sermons on the negative impacts of terrorism and religious militancy during the juma prayers of Friday and other religious occasions," said the minister. He said this would be done in line with the government's pledge to establish a digital Bangladesh by 2010
